Justice Karnan: Supreme Court issues bailable warrant against Calcutta high court judge C S Karnan 
10-3-2017 
refused to abide by its order to be personally present before it +

NEW DELHI: In an unprecedented decision, the Supreme Court on Friday issued bailable warrant against sitting judge of Calcutta High Court judge C S Karnan after hein a contempt proceeding against him.A seven judge bench headed by chief Justice J S Khehar said that the bench was left with no option but to issue warrant against Justice Karnan to ensure his presence in court to face contempt charges for making baseless allegations against retired and sitting judges of Supreme Court and Madras high court.The apex court entrusted the task of serving the warrant to DGP of West Bengal and posted the case for hearing to March 31. It issued bailable warrant against Justice Karnan to the sum of Rs 10,000. 
